Dialogue: 10,0:02:48.36,0:02:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:50.25,0:02:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother, I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:59.33,0:03:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:01.78,0:03:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm scared!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:03.23,0:03:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Please help me!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:06.44,0:03:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:23.40,0:03:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:27.83,0:03:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That must be it.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.12,0:03:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Is something wrong with that tree?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:36.00,0:03:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard it's been struck by lightning multiple times.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.60,0:03:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It must trouble you and your family.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:41.75,0:03:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought there may be an underlying cause.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:47.65,0:03:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of a cause?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.16,0:03:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Although that tree is magnificent,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:52.47,0:03:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,there are other large trees in its vicinity.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:55.96,0:03:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it's possible that it's been struck by lightning so many times
Dialogue: 10,0:03:59.35,0:04:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because other factors are involved.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:04.64,0:04:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, it may be inhabited by a mushi.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:09.78,0:04:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,A mushi?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:11.19,0:04:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:12.44,0:04:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Ginko, a mushi-shi.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:16.02,0:04:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So would it be possible for me \Nto see the tree in your backyard?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:23.20,0:04:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait here.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:25.89,0:04:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I must ask my husband first.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:35.19,0:04:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems there aren't any in this tree.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:37.92,0:04:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's the case...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:39.75,0:04:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,has anyone in your household been struck by lightning?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:53.43,0:04:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in, Reki.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:03.65,0:05:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, would you mind showing me your abdomen?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:12.77,0:05:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There it is.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:15.35,0:05:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever there's thunder and lightning,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:16.94,0:05:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,does it start to feel hot around your navel?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:22.92,0:05:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,How long ago was he hit by lightning?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:25.62,0:05:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The first time was five years ago,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:28.23,0:05:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,under that tree.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:31.24,0:05:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then, he's been hit about three more times...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:34.61,0:05:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,all while he was under that tree.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:39.33,0:05:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a miracle he survived.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:41.43,0:05:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:43.73,0:05:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:46.39,0:05:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,As I suspected, the cause is a mushi.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:50.51,0:05:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It is?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:53.45,0:05:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a Shouraishi, \Nor "Lightning Summoner" mushi.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:56.05,0:06:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Typically, it hovers in the sky \Nand eats lightning to sustain itself.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:01.41,0:06:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,However, its larvae sometimes fall \Nto the surface when lightning strikes.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:10.24,0:06:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,After a Shouraishi larva falls, \Nit is unable to return to the sky on its own.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:14.50,0:06:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It may therefore hide in a nearby tree hollow,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:17.28,0:06:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,or if a person is nearby,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:18.78,0:06:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it may enter his body through the navel \Nand hide there instead.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:22.44,0:06:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,While it remains in its host's body,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:24.57,0:06:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it discharges electricity \Nand calls lightning down to it.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:27.97,0:06:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It does so in order to eat the lightning and eventually emerge as an adult.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:31.72,0:06:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:34.21,0:06:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the Shouraishi eats lightning,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:36.85,0:06:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the host may be struck by lightning, \Nbut he does not usually die as a result.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:42.29,0:06:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if it continues to happen,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:44.36,0:06:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it will eventually prove fatal.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:47.97,0:06:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,When there is lightning, it would be best if he hid in a nearby cave of some sort.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:52.72,0:06:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I often tell him to go into the cellar,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.72,0:06:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but he refuses to listen.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.48,0:07:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there are ways to extract the Shouraishi from him.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:04.13,0:07:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We would simply need to make \Nan infusion out of his umbilical cord.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:08.55,0:07:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's all right, may we use it to help him?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.13,0:07:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but I'm not quite sure where I put it...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:16.44,0:07:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Shino!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:17.60,0:07:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you always like this?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:20.26,0:07:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Reki's life we're talking about here!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:22.56,0:07:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Find it immediately!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:25.52,0:07:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay—
Dialogue: 10,0:07:25.93,0:07:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.22,0:07:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind it.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:45.99,0:07:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Reki, please return to your room for now.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.85,0:07:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry about that.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:58.05,0:08:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm certain she has it somewhere around here.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:00.36,0:08:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you wait here for her?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.60,0:08:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, I must get back to work myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:08.76,0:08:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's not too rude, I'd like to ask a personal question.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:13.30,0:08:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Are your wife and son related by blood?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:17.04,0:08:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:21.41,0:08:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife seems to struggle \Nwith how to relate to our son.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:27.89,0:08:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,However, she {\i1}did{\i0} give birth to him.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:51.57,0:08:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:53.68,0:08:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:57.76,0:08:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Please help me!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:00.04,0:09:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to go through \Nwith this arranged marriage.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:05.35,0:09:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There's someone else I wish to marry!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.80,0:09:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:13.56,0:09:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:33.70,0:09:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Shino!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:38.79,0:09:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the meaning of this?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:46.48,0:09:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to have this child.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:55.64,0:09:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.57,0:10:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure I won't love him.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:52.76,0:10:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Come inside.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:58.47,0:10:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not safe up there.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:06.21,0:11:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Reki?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:41.03,0:11:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you looking at?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:49.27,0:11:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The clouds.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.44,0:11:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,How's it look?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:52.57,0:11:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think any of them are thunder clouds?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:56.58,0:11:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:59.19,0:12:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:01.00,0:12:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine weather.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:04.69,0:12:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So,{for emphasis} are you always on the lookout for thunder clouds?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:10.18,0:12:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:13.24,0:12:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, why don't you ever try to run away from the lightning?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:16.00,0:12:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you scared?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:20.61,0:12:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I am.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:24.39,0:12:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But I like it.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.07,0:12:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's strong, and it's beautiful too.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:33.64,0:12:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither Father nor Mother look me in the eye.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.76,0:12:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But the lightning does. It always comes right for me.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:49.33,0:12:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, you can't predict the time when it might kill you.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:55.92,0:12:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:59.20,0:13:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It would have been better \Nif I'd never been born anyway.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:20.04,0:13:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you find it?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:23.43,0:13:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nowhere to be found...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:28.04,0:13:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I must have been careless and thrown it away somehow.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:34.12,0:13:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There are other means.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:36.88,0:13:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We can even open him up to remove it.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:39.68,0:13:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I'm not certain \Nyour son will allow us to do that.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:48.88,0:13:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because he's angry at his mother... \Nfor being this way.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:59.80,0:14:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why he has lightning strike right in front of me...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:03.14,0:14:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He is punishing me.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:10.31,0:14:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And why shouldn't he?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.96,0:14:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm his mother,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:14.94,0:14:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet I haven't shown him any real affection.{i joe. no, he totsu}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:20.66,0:14:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Still,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:22.31,0:14:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I just don't know how
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.19,0:14:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to love him.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:36.18,0:14:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what's going on here.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:38.93,0:14:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He is punishing me.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:43.00,0:14:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is that really what he's doing?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:46.71,0:14:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is that really why he sits up there, \Non that tree, and calls lightning down to himself?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:55.24,0:14:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, buddy!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:57.78,0:15:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You should stay away from that tree!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:00.64,0:15:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It attracts lightning!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:03.67,0:15:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:04.62,0:15:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:06.07,0:15:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's sunny, so it should be fine, \Ndon't you think?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:09.19,0:15:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The clouds are already forming, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:11.96,0:15:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Clouds around here get huge in no time.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:15.27,0:15:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So just be careful.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:17.24,0:15:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's get going.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:19.04,0:15:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:20.84,0:15:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Knock on wood.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.81,0:15:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:07.00,0:16:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever asked him why he waits for the lightning
Dialogue: 10,0:16:11.35,0:16:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,specifically on top of that tree?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:17.32,0:16:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I already know the answer.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:21.72,0:16:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There's another possible explanation.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:25.14,0:16:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}That tree, specifically, poses the lowest risk \Nof others' being harmed by the lightning that strikes him.{and yes, this apostrophe is correct. http://www.quickanddirtytips.com/education/grammar/do-i-hate-your-singing-or-you-singing}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.03,0:16:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It is also relatively far from your home,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:35.16,0:16:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,so the house is always safe from the lightning.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.23,0:16:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, however,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:42.39,0:16:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it's close enough for him to rush to \Nas soon as he notices lightning approaching.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:48.13,0:16:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, whenever the villagers hear thunder,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:49.95,0:16:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,they know to stay away from that tree.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:57.99,0:16:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You're saying...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:59.78,0:17:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you never once considered that possibility?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:16.02,0:17:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He still hasn't gotten back yet.{"still" plus "yet" implies that he may have thought to himself sooner that the boy hadn't gotten home yet.}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:21.06,0:17:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea where he might have gone?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:24.40,0:17:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:27.11,0:17:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He may intend to call the lightning down elsewhere so that I cannot interfere.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:33.22,0:17:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there any other places \Nwhere it may be easy for him to do so?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:36.40,0:17:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,An open area with few people, for instance.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:41.33,0:17:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a meadow on the outskirts of the village.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:44.12,0:17:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:45.07,0:17:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to stop him.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.37,0:17:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:49.60,0:17:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to come too.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:52.71,0:17:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't listen to me anyway.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:56.72,0:17:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the only one who can stop him.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:59.83,0:18:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It {\i1}has{\i0} to be you.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:29.43,0:18:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:38.05,0:18:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:41.28,0:18:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You might die.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:45.97,0:18:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:57.90,0:19:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, you've got to be more direct with him!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:01.65,0:19:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell him that you want him to live!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:23.78,0:19:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:27.97,0:19:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:30.44,0:19:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't bring myself to think that way.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:50.61,0:19:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother—
Dialogue: 10,0:19:51.26,0:19:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.32,0:19:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's die together, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:00.20,0:20:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In my next life,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.64,0:20:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure I'll be born as a mother who can properly love her child.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:39.08,0:20:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He protected you.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:42.36,0:20:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:45.81,0:20:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet you still...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:52.15,0:20:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:32.68,0:21:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}After that,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:35.56,0:21:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}their son was taken in by a relative.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:42.50,0:21:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Perhaps that was the path this particular mother and her child had to take.
